- Build and run the test suite
- Update the version number in wscript
- Update the API version number in include/clogs/core.h
- Update the Changelog
- Nuke old versions: rm -rf /usr/local/share/doc/clogs /usr/local/lib/libclogs*
- On machines with 480 GTX and R9 270
  - Install the new version
  - rm -rf ~/.cache/clogs
  - clogs-tune --cl-gpu
  - Run benchmark
- Update clogs-benchmark-plot.sh with new version and run it
- Add the new benchmarks to git
- Run './waf dist' and check that the new version can install cleanly
- Upload new documentation to Sourceforge page (install it first):
    rsync -va --delete /usr/local/share/doc/clogs/ bmerry@web.sourceforge.net:/home/project-web/clogs/htdocs/doc/
- Check that the wiki page is up to date
- Create a new version in trac
- Upload the tarball to the file release system
  - sftp bmerry@frs.sourceforge.net
  - cd /home/frs/project/clogs
  - mkdir <release>
  - cd <release>
  - put clogs-<release>.tar.bz2
- Mark the new release as the latest version
- Tag the release
